replies.body:
It feels like if you aren't a pure burst mage, you'll have shit AP scaling and heavy mana issues to deal any decent damage

{{champion:13}} {{champion:163}} {{champion:34}} {{champion:7}} all fall into this, having 50% AP scaling at best and only going past the base damage of their spells at 400 or so AP.

With that, these characters end up all building extremely similar paths

{{item:3001}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3135}} {{item:3020}} all provide more damage for these low-scalers than the stronger mage options, and the rest of the items are usually set in place from the start for their utility because it's the only thing they can provide in lieu of better scaling

{{champion:13}} {{item:3040}} {{item:3110}} 
{{champion:163}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3165}} 
{{champion:34}} {{item:3040}} {{item:3157}} 
{{champion:7}} {{item:3146}} {{item:3100}} 

With most mages being on the lower-half of the scaling spectrum, it would be nice to see some more active damage items besides the hextechs.
